The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for text classification and indexing, which are common topics in information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL). The focus on using metadata such as titles instead of full-text also suggests a stronger emphasis on information retrieval and natural language processing, hence the higher likelihood of cs.IR and cs.CL.
